1
00:00:02,000 --> 00:00:09,125
Tracekeep is a local second brain for Codex, turning completed conversations into sourced memory and action.

2
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:11,703
Use Codex as usual.

3
00:00:11,703 --> 00:00:14,685
This is the default daily entry point.

4
00:00:14,685 --> 00:00:19,800
You do not need to say "remember this" or prefix a message with "Tracekeep."

5
00:00:19,800 --> 00:00:25,757
When a meaningful turn completes, a trusted local hook classifies the result.

6
00:00:25,757 --> 00:00:32,997
Durable conclusions become sourced Learning Notes; actions, decisions, and uncertain items become proposals the user can review.

7
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:39,275
Then ask inside Codex what unfinished work deserves attention today.

8
00:00:39,275 --> 00:00:47,397
Tracekeep returns a short, focused list from the local store, with the original source and a concrete next action.

9
00:00:47,397 --> 00:00:50,816
No browsing through folders or lists is required.

10
00:00:50,816 --> 00:00:57,656
The user stays in the conversation instead of opening a dashboard just to remember what mattered.

11
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:08,127
Ask Tracekeep to resume one open loop, and it reconnects the earlier decision, what is still missing, and what to do next.

12
00:01:08,127 --> 00:01:12,560
Codex can draft the next step while Tracekeep keeps the loop open.

13
00:01:12,560 --> 00:01:18,840
When the reply arrives, tell Codex to update or close it, and the local history stays reversible.

14
00:01:18,840 --> 00:01:22,165
Nothing is sent externally, and the source remains visible.

15
00:01:25,500 --> 00:01:30,899
A local Stop hook calls tracekeepd through an authenticated loopback API.

16
00:01:30,899 --> 00:01:36,298
Tracekeepd alone writes SQLite; sources, evidence, and FTS5 search stay local.

17
00:01:36,298 --> 00:01:41,207
Capture begins after installation and never claims every historical chat.

18
00:01:41,207 --> 00:01:44,642
Direct ChatGPT integration is planned, not shipped.

19
00:01:45,500 --> 00:01:51,513
The Web Dashboard is only the supporting workspace for batch review, evidence, backup, and settings.

20
00:01:51,513 --> 00:01:59,530
Here the user can inspect a proposed action, accept it, edit it, reject it, merge duplicates, or undo a change.

21
00:01:59,530 --> 00:02:02,737
It is not the required daily entry point.

22
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:12,822
Tracekeep itself was built end to end in Codex with GPT-5.6.

23
00:02:12,822 --> 00:02:18,000
From the product owner's problem and trust boundaries, Codex coordinated focused subagents

24
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:23,000
for requirements, interaction design, architecture, and implementation,

25
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:28,741
then regression tests, synthetic UAT, privacy review, Windows packaging, and documentation.

26
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:38,166
Codex also handled GitHub commits, pull requests, CI, release assets, captions, narration, and submission preparation.

27
00:02:38,166 --> 00:02:47,243
Public PRs show automatic capture, the Windows release, and competition materials moving from decisions to a tested, downloadable product.
